msgstr "Súmáil socraithe go: %1"

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:232
msgid ""
"This sets an empty User-Agent stylesheet, and expects the document "
"stylesheet to style everything (which publishers probably don't).\n"
"This is mostly only interesting for testing."
msgstr ""
"Socraíonn sé seo stílbileog Úsáideora-Ghníomhaire folamh, agus táthar ag "
"súil go stíleoidh stílbileog an doiciméid gach rud (nach ndéanann "
"foilsitheoirí is dócha).\n"
"Níl suim ag baint leis seo ach le haghaidh tástála den chuid is mó."

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:235
#: plugins/kosync.koplugin/main.lua:114
msgid "Auto"
msgstr "Uath"

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:237
msgid ""
"This selects the default and preferred stylesheet for the document type."
msgstr ""
"Roghnaíonn sé seo an bhileog stíl réamhshocraithe agus is fearr don chineál "
"doiciméid."

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:251
msgid "Traditional book look (epub.css)"
msgstr "Cuma traidisiúnta leabhair (epub.css)"

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:253
msgid ""
"This is our book look-alike stylesheet: it extends the HTML standard "
"stylesheet with styles aimed at making HTML content look more like a paper "
"book (with justified text and indentation on paragraphs) than like a web "
"page.\n"
"It is perfect for unstyled books, and might make styled books more "
"readable.\n"
"It may cause some small issues on some books (miscentered titles, headings "
"or separators, or unexpected text indentation), as publishers don't expect "
"to have our added styles at play and need to reset them; try switching to "
"html5.css when you notice such issues."
msgstr ""
"Seo ár mbileog stíle cosúil le leabhar: leathnaíonn sé an bhileog stíle "
"caighdeánach HTML le stíleanna atá dírithe ar ábhar HTML a dhéanamh níos "
"cosúla le leabhar páipéir (le téacs údaraithe agus eangú ar mhíreanna) ná le "
"leathanach gréasáin.\n"
"Tá sé foirfe do leabhair gan stíl, agus d'fhéadfadh sé leabhair stíle a "
"dhéanamh níos inléite.\n"
"D'fhéadfadh sé roinnt fadhbanna beaga a chruthú ar roinnt leabhar (teidil, "
"ceannteidil nó deighilteoirí mílárnaithe, nó eangú téacs gan choinne), toisc "
"nach mbíonn súil ag foilsitheoirí go mbeidh ár stíleanna breise i bhfeidhm "
"agus go gcaithfidh siad iad a athshocrú; déan iarracht aistriú go html5.css "
"nuair a thugann tú faoi deara fadhbanna den sórt sin."

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:263
msgid "HTML Standard rendering (html5.css)"
msgstr "Rindreáil chaighdeánach HTML (html5.css)"

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:265
msgid ""
"This stylesheet conforms to the HTML Standard rendering suggestions (with a "
"few limitations), similar to what most web browsers use.\n"
"As most publishers nowadays make and test their book with tools based on web "
"browser engines, it is the stylesheet to use to see a book as these "
"publishers intended.\n"
"On unstyled books though, it may give them the look of a web page (left "
"aligned paragraphs without indentation and with spacing between them); try "
"switching to epub.css when that happens."
msgstr ""
"Cloíonn an stílbhileog seo leis na moltaí rindreála Caighdeánach HTML (le "
"roinnt teorainneacha), cosúil leis an méid a úsáideann formhór na "
"mbrabhsálaithe gréasáin.\n"
"Ós rud é go ndéanann agus go dtástálann formhór na bhfoilsitheoirí a leabhar "
"le huirlisí atá bunaithe ar innill bhrabhsálaithe gréasáin na laethanta seo, "
"is í an stílbhileog í le húsáid chun leabhar a fheiceáil mar a bhí "
"beartaithe ag na foilsitheoirí seo.\n"
"Ar leabhair gan stíl, áfach, féadfaidh sé cuma leathanaigh ghréasáin a "
"thabhairt dóibh (míreanna ailínithe ar chlé gan eangú agus le spásáil "
"eatarthu); déan iarracht aistriú go epub.css nuair a tharlaíonn sé sin."

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:275
msgid "FictionBook (fb2.css)"
msgstr "Leabhar Ficsean (fb2.css)"

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:277
msgid ""
"This stylesheet is to be used only with FB2 and FB3 documents, which are not "
"classic HTML, and need some specific styling.\n"
"(FictionBook 2 & 3 are open XML-based e-book formats which originated and "
"gained popularity in Russia.)"
msgstr ""
"Níl an stílbhileog seo le húsáid ach le doiciméid FB2 agus FB3, nach HTML "
"clasaiceach iad, agus a bhfuil stíliú sonrach ag teastáil uathu.\n"
"(Is formáidí ríomhleabhar oscailte bunaithe ar XML iad FictionBook 2 & 3 a "
"tháinig chun cinn agus a fuair tóir sa Rúis.)"

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:290
msgid ""
"This stylesheet is obsolete: don't use it. It is kept solely to be able to "
"open documents last read years ago and to migrate their highlights."
msgstr ""
"Tá an stílbhileog seo as dáta: ná húsáid í. Coinnítear í go heisiach chun go "
"mbeidh tú in ann doiciméid a léadh blianta ó shin a oscailt agus chun a "
"gcuid buaicphointí a aistriú."

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:301
msgid "This is a user added stylesheet."
msgstr "Is bileog stíle curtha leis ag úsáideoir í seo."

#: frontend/apps/reader/modules/readertypeset.lua:307
msgid "Obsolete"
msgstr "As dáta"

